<paragraph id="8B888D405A3CFF939FF807FBE4410C8B" blockId="17.[189,310,948,974]" box="[189,310,948,974]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading id="D0C03A2C5A3CFF939FF807FBE4410C8B" bold="true" box="[189,310,948,974]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94351525A3CFF939FF807FBE4410C8B" bold="true" box="[189,310,948,974]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B888D405A3CFF939FF807ACE15A0BCF" blockId="17.[189,1399,995,1162]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="4C37F6C35A3CFF939FF807ACE4F10CB8" authority="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete, 2017" authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" box="[189,390,995,1021]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="desseinii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94351525A3CFF939FF807ACE4F10CB8" box="[189,390,995,1021]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Astiella desseinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A270EC295A3CFF939ECB07ACE49F0CB8" box="[398,488,995,1021]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C37F6C35A3CFF939D2807ACE79B0CB8" authority="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete, 2017" authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" box="[621,748,995,1021]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94351525A3CFF939D2807ACE79B0CB8" box="[621,748,995,1021]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A270EC295A3CFF939DB107ACE6390CB8" box="[756,846,995,1021]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having sessile flowers, elongated placentas, ovoid capsules, identical seed and pollen morphology, but differs in the erect habit (vs creeping), the linear leaves with secondary veins invisible (vs ovate to broadly ovate leaves with prominent secondary veins), and the cylindrical corolla tubes with the stamens exserted beyond the corolla throat in brevistylous flowers (vs funnel-shaped corolla tubes with the stamens always included).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32DDECB5A3CFF939FF800FFE45C0A59" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B888D405A3CFF939FF800FFE4330B8F" blockId="17.[189,324,1200,1226]" box="[189,324,1200,1226]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading id="D0C03A2C5A3CFF939FF800FFE4330B8F" bold="true" box="[189,324,1200,1226]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94351525A3CFF939FF800FFE4330B8F" bold="true" box="[189,324,1200,1226]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B888D405A3CFF939FF80090E45C0A59" blockId="17.[189,1399,1247,1308]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The species is named in honour of Dr. Steven Dessein, who was the first to observe and collect 
<taxonomicName id="4C37F6C35A3CFF939A580090E4530A59" authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="desseinii">
<emphasis id="B94351525A3CFF939A580090E4530A59" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Astiella desseinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
